the beginning of the equality-friendly reform with the Introduction of the Law and approved in the Constitutional Assembly sustained by the three political parties in Government.
The Law approved on June 25th, 2015, enacts equal protection of all families and all children with the effect of giving more options to others, including those excluded by the traditional family model. This already provides that in the adoption of a child, equality requirements for all people are respected in all areas of life (school, office, health, etc.). The law also obviates the need to base these requirements on their binding requirements to being a parent without sanctioning other forms and looking at their interests. The main novelty introduced concerns the guarantee of children’s right to live in a family consisting of parents of different or same sex. The law leaves intact the possibility of opting for those who, at the time of adoption, share a life and a home, establishing the possibility of adoption in the minority of cases than set by a previous law. All rights also established by the law for the parent-child bond through the mother or the father remain intact.
A second major event for San Marino is the completion of Education Reform. The Law introduces the opportunity to offer the subjects in order to get two diplomas: a University Diploma and the APE.
